reg_info.full_title: O. Reg. 103/11: DEEMING ORDER (CENTRAL ALMAGUIN PLANNING BOARD)
reg_info.act_under: Planning Act   Loi sur l’aménagement du territoire

content.content: 1. (1) Ontario Regulation 501/96, as it read immediately before this Regulation comes into force, shall be deemed to be and to always have been a by-law passed under section 34 of the Act by the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 1 (1). (2) The deemed by-law shall be referred to as by-law number 2011-01 of the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 1 (2).
content.raw_html:
1. (1) Ontario Regulation 501/96, as it read immediately before this Regulation comes into force, shall be deemed to be and to always have been a by-law passed under section 34 of the Act by the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 1 (1).

(2) The deemed by-law shall be referred to as by-law number 2011-01 of the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 1 (2).

content.content: 2. (1) Ontario Regulation 516/98, as it read immediately before this Regulation comes into force, shall be deemed to be and to always have been a by-law passed under section 34 of the Act by the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 2 (1). (2) The deemed by-law shall be referred to as by-law number 2011-02 of the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 2 (2).
content.raw_html:
2. (1) Ontario Regulation 516/98, as it read immediately before this Regulation comes into force, shall be deemed to be and to always have been a by-law passed under section 34 of the Act by the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 2 (1).

(2) The deemed by-law shall be referred to as by-law number 2011-02 of the Central Almaguin Planning Board. O. Reg. 103/11, s. 2 (2).

content.content: 3. Omitted (provides for coming into force of provisions of this Regulation). O. Reg. 103/11, s. 3.
